<TEXT>
health officials are blaming contaminated food for 
an outbreak of salmonella poisoning that killed seven residents of 
a geriatric hospital and sickened 160 others 
the preliminary findings released wednesday by frances public 
hospital authority indicated food preparation at the charles richet 
hospital in suburban cergy pontoise was not the cause of the 
outbreak 
salmonella poisoning struck nearly one quarter of the hospitals 
670 patients shortly after a sept 28 dinner of a soup including 
ground beef followed by an omelette with rice pudding for dessert 
since friday two women and five men aged 85 to 93 have died 
from food poisoning the remaining 160 infected patients are not in 
lifethreatening danger the health authority said in a statement 
residents at the hospital are longterm patients suffering 
serious illness or handicaps the health authority said 
an investigation conducted by the pasteur institute will attempt 
to pinpoint the exact cause of the poisoning the health authority 
said the results will not be known for several days 
the mass poisoning is the second in france in three months nine 
patients at a retirement home at la rochelle in western france died 
over a onemonth period after eating salmonellainfected rice 
pudding july 9 
there were 6000 reported cases of salmonella poisoning in 
france during 1988 health officials said 
</TEXT>
