<TEXT>
president bushs approval rating remains high 
although a majority feel his administration is lagging in the war 
on drugs the budget deficit and pollution according to a 
washington postabc news poll 
bushs approval rating as president stood at 76 percent among 
the 1535 adults interviewed at random for the survey which was 
conducted between sept 28 and oct 3 and reported on in thursday 
editions of the newspaper 
other recent polls have show similar high approval ratings for 
bush 
in the war on drugs 56 percent said the administration is not 
doing all it can 68 percent held a similar view on the budget 
deficit and 71 percent said not enough was being done to combat 
pollution 
however 61 percent approved of the way bush is dealing with the 
nations environmental problems and 72 percent approved of his 
handling of foreign affairs 
the poll has a margin of error of plus or minus three percentage 
points 
</TEXT>
