<TEXT>
prime minister margaret thatcher was asked over 
lunch with foreign journalists how shed run a political campaign 
against margaret thatcher 
her reply 
i wouldnt id vote for her 
this instant response on wednesday showed the british prime 
minister in full combative cry as she goes into the 198990 
political season with three consecutive election victories behind 
her and every indication she will go for a fourth 
autumn in britain means the annual party conventions where 
political leaders take stock of the year and promise victory next 
time 
mrs thatchers conservatives convene next week the opposition 
labor party is halfway through its convention buoyed by opinion 
poll leads and a conviction that after a decade of thatcherism the 
british are ready for a change 
mrs thatcher obviously disagrees but she does so with the zeal 
and enthusiasm of a firsttime candidate rather than a senior 
stateswoman who turns 64 this month and is the longestserving 
leader of a western democracy 
she has been to poland and talked to farmers who cant get 
permits for equipment to grow crops last month she was in siberia 
watching soviets selling vodka to her press party strictly for 
hard currency she had her sixth meeting with mikhail s gorbachev 
and was struck once again she says by the enormous risks of 
switching rapidly from communism to a free market 
her conclusion is characteristically simple there is no 
revision refashioning or reform of socialism that is possible 
theres only rejection of it 
this unwavering conviction that she is right is a thatcher 
hallmark and any suggestion of second thoughts is quickly slapped 
down 
lately attempts are being made to penetrate the thatcher 
mystique through longdistance psychoanalysis leo abse a former 
labor lawmaker has just published a 288page book whose central 
thesis is that mrs thatcher suffers from narcissism caused by an 
unloving mother 
on wednesday the independent newspaper said mrs thatcher plans 
to block her official residence with 10foothigh railings it said 
psychiatrists believed it was a sign of the stress caused by 10 
years at the helm 
mrs thatcher probably would scoff at such notions she believes 
she simply represents basic human instincts 
thatcherism is a lot older than me she said 
referring to britains bumpy passage into the brotherhood of 
european nations she said she merely wanted to make sure the 
european economic community followed thatcherite principles namely 
not to tie free enterprise down in bureaucracy 
because we approached the whole of europe in the same way as 
we do at home we dont wish it to be tied up with unnecessary 
regulations she said 
mrs thatcher likes to illustrate her points with mundane 
examples like the polish farmers last year she had asked them why 
they couldnt grow enough food they told her it was because of the 
difficulty in obtaining farming equipment from officials 
and then it suddenly dawned on me mrs thatcher said 
that it is the whole network of intricate controls which will 
stop people from being able to make maximum use of their property 
</TEXT>
