<TEXT>
mikhail baryshnikov gave an exciting performance 
in american document at the opening night gala of the martha 
graham dance company 
baryshnikov danced as though born to the graham technique 
although his training is in ballet which is much different 
cecilia peck a student at the graham school and daughter of 
actor gregory peck narrated the dance a celebration of democracy 
which miss graham choreographed originally in 1938 and revised this 
year 
the 95yearold choreographer took bows with the company after 
the performance tuesday night at the city center and the audience 
responded with a standing ovation 
baryshnikov and maxine sherman danced the roles of an 
everyman couple who move through the history of america both 
were modest but eager stalwart and optimistic their duets from 
embattled through proud to beautifully romantic were a high point 
of american document 
in the original production the parts were danced by miss graham 
and erich hawkins 
joyce herring in red danced the counterpart to the narrator 
in revising the dance miss graham changed the chorus from the 
original all women to nine women and eight men she also integrated 
the speaking and dancing more smoothly and she changed the music 
american document is danced to from a score by ray green to 
concerto for oboe and orchestra by john corigliano 
bert lucarelli was oboe soloist and stanley sussman conducted 
the evening began with night chant from 1988 and ended with 
the rite of spring from 1984 both choreographed by miss graham 
the company will dance at the city center through oct 22 
