fearing they might miss the last 
train to the west hundreds of east germans scuffled with 
czechoslovak police to get to the west german embassy many 
refugees were injured 
the desperate struggle came hours before east germany sought to 
curb the exodus of refugees on tuesday banning its citizens from 
traveling to czechoslovakia without a visa 
however east germany also decided tuesday to permit the about 
10000 east germans around the embassy compound to emigrate to the 
west 
hundreds of east germans overturned a police barricade and 
scaled facades rooftops or a 6foot spiked fence in an effort to 
reach the crowded embassy compound which had been closed earlier 
tuesday 
police swung their nightsticks and clubbed like mad one 
czechoslovak witness reported many refugees were left 
bloodspattered 
more people from the waiting crowd surged toward where the 
beatings took place refugees quickly built a human ladder to 
help many clear the fence witnesses said 
some became caught on the fences sharp spikes while others 
jumped or fell headfirst to the ground some were later seen lying 
unconscious inside the compound the witnesses said 
outside the embassy families with small children were unable to 
get inside 
this is pandemonium said a red cross assistant handling 
injured refugees on the embassy grounds 
