<TEXT>
through a combination of cunning ruthlessness 
and oldfashioned good fortune panamas gen manuel antonio 
noriega has survived yet another challenge to his rule 
but whatever sense of triumph noriega felt tuesday after the 
defeat of a military uprising against him most experts believe he 
is weaker now than at any time since assuming the command of the 
defense forces more than six years ago 
the panamanian economy is a wreck noriegas base of support has 
never been narrower his diplomatic isolation is almost complete 
and he rules over one of the most alienated populations anywhere in 
the hemisphere 
noriega has won points among some panamanians by surviving the 
unrelenting hostility of the united states and among this group 
noriegas ability thus far to win the test of wills with washington 
may have left him standing taller than ever 
but how far can noriega continue to coast on his 
antiamericanism at some point it appears the combination of 
pressures against him eventually will oust him 
those pressures are formidable indeed in early 1988 after 
noriega deposed yet a second president in two years who showed an 
independent streak the reagan administration moved decisively 
against him 
it froze all panamanian assets in the united states withheld 
payments to the government relating to panama canal operations and 
imposed trade sanctions against the country all this has 
contributed to panamas impoverishment 
after a period in which the united states looked to noriega for 
help in its effort to bring down nicaraguas leftist government 
washington has since done virtually everything in its power to 
remove him short of invasion president bush insisted tuesday that 
the united states was not behind the antinoriega insurrection 
besides pinching him hard economically the administration has 
campaigned tirelessly against him internationally and tried to 
intimidate him by expanding the size of the us military 
establishment based in panama 
at a different level panamas image was sullied by the us 
drug trafficking indictments against noriega and was damaged even 
more by the elections in may when government authorities tossed out 
the returns rather than acknowledge the defeat of the pronoriega 
candidate for good measure government agents assaulted opposition 
candidates 10 days after the balloting 
even the organization of american states not known for taking 
decisive stands blamed noriega for the abuses surrounding the 
elections and called for a democratic transfer of power 
the oas effort has since been suspended but noriegas 
international acceptance appears to be at an alltime low the most 
recent blow occurred on sept 1 when the noriegacontrolled council 
of state named a noriega crony as president of panama it was the 
second time in 18 months that noriega engineered the appointment of 
a president with no visible qualifications for the job 
there is little support around the hemisphere for overt us 
military action against noriega after all there is no apparent 
danger to the operation of the canal and beyond that there is 
strong support in the hemisphere for the notion that outsiders 
should not intervene in the internal affairs of any nation 
but noriega is testing the patience of countries which are the 
most enthusiastic supporters of that principle even mexico whose 
president carlos salinas de gortari was with bush when word of 
the uprising in panama reached here tuesday is keeping its 
diplomatic distance from panama 
although mexico keeps an ambassador in panama city mexican 
officials have told us diplomats they intend to raise their 
concerns about noriegas continued rule with panamanian authorities 
</TEXT>
