<TEXT>
a second type of deadly aids virus has 
reached the west coast where it was found in a west african man 
who often failed to wear condoms when he had sex with 20 to 40 
women here since 1979 officials say 
this is the first case of hiv2 to our knowledge in the 
western united states said dr david ho director of the aids 
virology laboratory at cedarssinai medical center 
hiv2 or human immunodeficiency virus type 2 is common in 
west africa but very rare in the united states where almost all 
of more than 105000 aids cases were caused by the hiv1 type 
the infected man a los angeles resident who moved here from 
sierra leone in 1979 hasnt developed aids and chances are low 
