the principal tasks of the nearly 13000 us 
military forces in panama are to protect both the panama canal and 
the estimated 40000 american civilians living in that country 
these forces are precluded from involvement in panamanian 
internal affairs but panamanian officials have said us troops 
frequently have been used in maneuvers designed to intimidate the 
government 
under the panama canal treaties us forces are allowed to 
patrol only their own bases and areas under joint uspanamanian 
jurisdiction 
there were about 10800 us military personnel in panama early 
this year but president bush augmented that number by 2000 after a 
postelection outbreak of violence in panama 
the us southern command responsible for all us military 
activities in central and south america is headquartered at quarry 
heights one of 10 major military installations in panama 
