<TEXT>
good news for harried parents of toddlers the 1990 nissan 
axxess minivan is especially for you 
the axxess is the first small van with a sliding passenger door 
on each side of the vehicle and that makes it easy for parents to 
extricate little ones from the back seat 
forget about folding yourself in two and climbing inside to get 
at the kids with the axxess handy doors you can just reach in 
from either side imagine how this could cut down on wailing time 
and no need to worry about the young ones opening the doors as 
you drive both doors are fitted with childproof locks that allow 
opening only from the outside 
this vehicle also should appeal to buyers who want the 
versatility of a van and the safety of a car as nissan notes the 
axxess is the first minivan that meets safety standards for 
passenger carsvans are categorized as trucks under federal 
regulations and therefore need not meet the more rigid car safety 
guidelines 
the axxess however has 5mph bumpers a highmounted rear 
brake light sidedoor beams for protection in side crashes 
passive seatbelts up front and threepoint seat belts in back all 
standard equipment 
although available in frontdrive mode the nissan axxess offers 
even better traction with its allwheeldrive version which was 
the test vehicle in a sudden thunderstorm the axxess 
allwheeldrive offered surefooted control and peace of mind 
because of its size bigger than a sedan but smaller than other 
minivans the vehicle also maneuvered easily 
the allwheeldrive test model was powered by the standard 
24liter fourcylinder engine that produced 138 horsepower and 
was paired with a fourspeed automatic overdrive transmission 
the axxess wouldnt win acceleration derbies and i noticed a 
couple of jerks as i put it through some paces and the transmission 
sought the right gear but the fuel economy of 18 mpg in the city 
and 22 mpg on the highway is close to that of other 
twowheeldrive minivans 
for example mazdas mpv with automatic transmission is rated at 
19 mpg in the city and 24 mpg on the highway while the plymouth 
voyager automatic with fourcylinder engine gets 21 mpg in the city 
and 23 mpg on the highway 
nissan expects axxess buyers to fit the young family profile 
the targeted median age for buyers is the mid30s and they are 
likely to have some college education with a household income of 
around 38000 they will be on a fairly tight budget said company 
spokesman ec mueller 
theyre not looking for something faddish they want quality 
and style he said nissan wanted to give them something thats 
comfortable fun to drive where you dont feel youre stuffed in a 
box 
thats why the axxess has so much glass the dashboard area is 
expansive and there are even tiny windows alongside the curving 
dash the sunroof on the test model added a feeling of space as 
did the headrests with holes cut in the middle i noted however 
that all that glass lets in a lot of sunlight and could quickly 
make for a hot interior on 90degree summer days thats where the 
air conditioning came in handy 
the test vehicle had seating for seven but rather than the 
typical minivan arrangement where two people sit in the middle and 
three in the back the axxess had a threepassenger seat in the 
middle and a twopassenger bench in back 
to reach the rearmost seat you must fold forward the seatback 
at one end of the middle seat then lift the entire folded middle 
seat forward against the front seat it took a little getting used 
to but worked well once i got the hang of it 
the rear door opened easily and offered access to a space behind 
the third seat big enough for several grocery bags to get more 
cargo room you must remove the rear seat headrests flip the seat 
cushion forward and the rear seatback down that too took a 
little practice 
minimum legroom for the rearmost seat made this position 
bestsuited for children the middle seat was better although the 
backs of the front seats still hit my legs if they were pushed all 
the way back and reclined a bit 
nissan expects us sales of about 18000 in the 1989 and 1990 
model years combined the axxess made its us debut in late march 
and sales through the first six months totaled more than 2000 the 
axxess has been sold as the prairie in japan since september 1988 
because the axxess is a new vehicle consumer reports magazine 
does not list an owners trouble report 
