international business machines corp has 
announced software for supercomputers based on a patented 
breakthrough by a mathematician at atampt bell laboratories 
atampt introduced its own package of hardware and software based 
on the socalled karmarkar algorithm last year and it appears that 
ibms entry tuesday puts the two technology giants in direct 
competition 
an ibm press release made no mention of atampt and simply said 
that part of its softwares power stems from a new programming 
method which drew worldwide attention when it was introduced a few 
years ago 
ibm spokesman denis arvay who mentioned the atampt connection 
said ibm was entitled to use the atampt patent through a 
crosslicensing agreement between the companies 
atampt spokesman bob ford said he could not find anyone at atampt 
who knew of the ibm product and thus the company had no comment on 
it 
the karmarkar algorithm invented in 1984 by atampts narendra 
karmarkar is a programming method for solving resourceallocation 
problems that involve huge numbers of variables such as scheduling 
daily crew assignments for a major airline 
ibm said its software was able to obtain the best solution to an 
airline scheduling problem in less time than a cray 2 supercomputer 
from cray research inc reportedly took to solve a problem 
onetenth the size 
ibms software known as the optimization subroutine library 
runs on big 3090 mainframe computers that have addon equipment to 
make them work as supercomputers but ibm said versions of it can 
run on smaller ibm computers even its personal computers 
the chief creators of ibms software were john tomlin of ibms 
almaden research center in san jose calif and john forrest of 
the thomas j watson research center in yorktown heights ny 
atampts hardwaresoftware product korbx was introduced in 
august 1988 at a price of 89 million so far there are two 
customers willing to have their names publicized the military 
airlift command and delta air lines inc 
