international business machines corp says it 
will make available a program that checks for viruses in personal 
computers responding in part to customer worries about an 
impending attack 
news reports about the socalled datacrime virus which is 
programmed to attack after oct 12 have caused widespread alarm 
even though experts say the virus is rare and a relatively small 
number of personal computers will be harmed 
up until the recent press hype our customers had not 
expressed any tremendous interest over and above what we already do 
in terms of security products and awareness said art gilbert 
ibms manager of secure systems industry support 
small companies in the antivirus field expressed support for 
the step tuesday by the worlds largest computer maker 
its about time one of the big boys realized what a problem 
this is and did something about it to date all the antivirus 
activity is being done by the mom and pops out there said ross 
greenberg a new yorkbased consultant and author of flushot plus 
its a very important and responsible step said pamela 
kane president of panda systems in wilmington del and author of 
a new book virus protection 
ibm said its ibm virus scanning program for computers that run 
microsoft corps dos baselayer software would spot three strains 
of the datacrime virus as well as more common viruses that go by 
such names as the jerusalem lehigh bouncing ball cascade and 
brain 
the program is available for 35 directly from ibm or from 
dealers marketing representatives and remarketers gilbert said 
the program will detect but not eradicate viruses some other 
companies say they have products that will eradicate viruses 
although others say such programs are not reliable 
gilbert said installing a virus checker is not a substitute for 
safecomputing practices such as making backup copies of programs 
and data and being cautious about software of unknown origin 
the datacrime virus cripples personal computers hard disks 
where programs and data are stored by wiping out the directory 
sections known as the partition table and file allocation table 
experts who have dismantled copies of the virus say it is set up 
to attack computers when their internal calendars go past oct 12 
the traditional date for columbus day 
