<TEXT>
the fair trade commission has raided apple 
computers major authorized dealers to investigate allegations that 
they pressured magazines to drop advertisements for discount stores 
selling apple products officials said wednesday 
on tuesday the ftc raided almost 40 sites including seven 
offices of canon sales co inc and apple computer japan japanese 
headquarters of the californiabased apple computer inc said 
mitsuru suzuki an ftc investigator 
canon and apple computer denied the allegations 
an official at the ministry of international trade and industry 
speaking on condition of anonymity said the ftc could warn but 
not punish any companies found to have applied such pressure 
suzuki said one nonauthorized retailer of apple products had 
filed a complaint accusing canon and apple computer japan of 
pressuring some major computer magazines not to publish such 
retailers ads featuring discounted apple computers 
its sabotage to free business activities suzuki said 
and we suspect apple might have been cooperating in the action 
which prevents equal opportunity for other competitors 
among the popular apple products involved are desktop computers 
such as macintosh plus and macintosh se printers including image 
writer ii hard discs and external drives for added memory capacity 
akisuke fukutomi an executive of step one of about 10 
individual importers of macintosh computers told the associated 
press that he filed the complaint with the ftc 
our company is the victim he said 
he said mac life a major computer magazine published by 
kawade shobo and featuring apple products carried one 
advertisement by step in april but then stopped 
the magazines editor apologized explaining that canon and 
apple pressured the magazine he said 
the editor could not be reached for comment 
we should be given equal opportunity so that everybody can 
compete on the same ground fukutomi said 
we have no fancy showrooms nor do we have beautiful 
brochures but our low pricing is reasonable and whats wrong with 
that he said 
for example a 4megabite macintosh se with japanese language 
capability costs 6030 through any of the 20 authorized agents 
whereas step sells it for 4200 he said 
since june another major monthly magazine ascii has left 
blank spaces in steps ads where there used to be prices 
step also carries nec epson and toshiba computers fukutomi 
said adding that it sells some 110 macs a month 
canon sales co was the sole agent for apple computers in japan 
until apples subsidiary was establisheed in 1983 canon does not 
import apple computers but distributes 80 percent to 90 percent of 
apple computers in japan to about 240 retail stores said motoyuki 
fujimoto a canon spokesman 
we are innocent and there is no evidence to merit such 
suspicion he said 
takashi fujimura canons managing director said in a 
statement were in a position to help the ftc investigate as 
well as conducting our own investigation internally 
the ftc also accused apple computer japan of refusing to repair 
apple products brought in by customers who had bought them from 
nonauthorized retailers 
