actively traded municipal bonds rose 316 to 92 the average yield 
to maturity fell to 738 percent from 740 percent late tuesday 
yields on threemonth treasury bills rose to 804 percent as the 
discount gained 3 basis points to 778 percent yields on sixmonth 
bills rose to 830 percent as the discount advanced 4 basis points 
to 787 percent yields on oneyear bills rose to 838 percent as 
the discount rose 2 basis points to 779 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks was quoted at 8 percent down from 9 percent late tuesday 
but analysts said the relatively low funds rate was due to 
technical conditions in the shortterm market for bank borrowings 
as wednesday marked the end of a bank reserve reporting period 
